Santa Clara County Public Health Department Black Infant Health (BIH) Program
Santa Clara County Public Health Department
Black Infant Health (BIH) Program
page.normal_text:
• In 1989, the BIH Program was established in response to the alarming rate of infant mortality among African Americans in California. In 1990, $3.4 million was allocated to fund 16 BIH sites where over 90% of African American births and deaths occurred in the state. Currently there are 17 BIH sites.
